      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a function that should parse the protocol correctly:\n\n```python\ndef parse_packet(data: bytes) -> dict:\n    if len(data) < 5:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid packet size\")\n    \n    if data[0] != 0xAA:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid header\")\n    \n    command_type = data[1]\n    value = (data[2] << 16) | data[3]\n    checksum = ~((data[0] << 8) | (command_type << 8) | (value >> 8)) & 0xFF\n    \n    # Correct the checksum for little-endian systems\n    if data[4] != checksum:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid checksum\")\n    \n    curses_map = {0x01: 'READ', 0x02: 'WRITE', 0x03: 'STATUS'}\n    return {'cmd': curses_map[command_type], 'val': value}\n```\n\nThis function first checks the header, then calculates the command type and value. It also calculates the checksum and checks if it matches the expected value. If the checksum is incorrect, it raises a ValueError. Finally, it maps the command type to a readable string and returns the dictionary.",
